In establishing the amount of the deposit required by subsection (1) of this section for a particular insurer, the commissioner shall consider the following factors:
The amount of Kentucky writings;
The amount of policy reserves and claim reserves pertaining to Kentucky risks;
The kind of insurance written in Kentucky;
The current financial and operating test results of the insurer provided by the National Association of Insurance Commissioners under its insurance regulatory information system; and
Any other relevant financial data.
